 # Changelog
 
+## 2026-07-16 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S0-P03-T008 (task/evidence/independent-review framework; S0 tooling)
+
+- Eighth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program (S0-P03), one task per run. Goal: guarantee one task = one result, rollbackable, machine-acceptable, and judged by an independent context. NOT_DEPLOYED, 0 recurring cloud cost; all tools are read-only and touch nothing in the worker/D1/production. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/: TASK_INDEX.csv (the 90-task machine index from the package 06_TASK_INDEX.csv) and tools/ -- check_dag.py (dependency DAG checker), validate_evidence.py (evidence schema validator), task_runner.py (one-task-one-result + dependency gate), EVIDENCE_TEMPLATE.md, README.md. Verified by tool self-tests (evidence test-results/tool_selftest.txt): check_dag = PASS (90 unique task_ids, 123 dependency edges, no dangling deps, acyclic); validate_evidence returns INCOMPLETE when evidence is missing and only ever the strongest status READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION (never PASS); task_runner returns BLOCKED_BY_DEPS when a dependency is not yet READY, READY when deps+evidence are complete, UNKNOWN_TASK for a bad id; and the validator flags implementer self-signed Stage-Gate PASS. Acceptance met: 90 task IDs unique and acyclic; missing evidence cannot be PASS; the implementer cannot self-sign a Stage Gate. This completes Stage S0's tooling; the remaining S0 step is the S0 Exit Owner gate (confirm the private-facts snapshot has no critical omission, incl. FACT-013 plan/billing and FACT-015 private branches). Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
+
 ## 2026-07-16 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S0-P02-T007 (Verified/Unknown/Assumption drift report)
 
 - Seventh task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program (last of S0-P02), one task per run. Goal: separate public facts, Owner directives, inferences, unknowns, and stale facts. Docs-only synthesis of T004/T005/T006; release_mode NOT_DEPLOYED, 0 recurring cloud cost; no drift fixed (only classified). Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/: FACT_LEDGER.csv (20 rows classified VERIFIED_PUBLIC/OWNER_DIRECTIVE/VERIFIED_PRIVATE/UNVERIFIED_PRIVATE/ASSUMPTION_NOT_REQUIREMENT/DRIFT/STALE/PARTIAL, each with verification_status + assigned_task_or_gate), DRIFT_REPORT.md (Verified/Unknown/Assumption/Stale/Drift sections), and BLOCKING_LIST.md (A blocking items -> S0 Exit Owner, B drifts -> named later tasks, C not-blocking, D hard rules). Acceptance: CSV parses to 20 rows; the only two UNVERIFIED facts (FACT-013 plan/billing, FACT-015 private branches) are both assigned to the S0 Exit Owner gate; no requirement may be derived from UNKNOWN and UNKNOWN != 0. Three drifts (DRIFT-FACT-006 source-truth, DRIFT-FACT-007 status-doc, DRIFT-FACT-011 D1 legacy tables) are routed to named later tasks, not fixed here. FACT-016's 20TB envelope is explicitly rebutted by the measured 1.05MB D1. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION. This completes S0-P02; next is S0-P03-T008 then the S0 Exit Owner gate.
